.TH STCHOWN 10 "August 2024" "1.0" "Neverdark Manual"
.SH NAME
stchown \- change ownership of a spacetime area
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBstchown\fI target shift [position]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Change the ownership of a spacetime area to \fItarget\fP.
.PP
This means that person will be able to develop a library
that defines things that happen for players on that area.
And to set rules on what the governors below him can do in
their own libraries.
.PP
shift is a number from 64 (entirety) to 0 (specific position).
.PP
Only those that own a containing area
can set ownership of those within.
.SH EXAMPLE
If root runs stchown david 63, then david will own half of all space.
And will also be able to define things that happen on special
events for those on that half.
.SH SEE ALSO
